modules.description: This module implements a syntax extension for embedding SPARQL queries directly in OCaml code, validating their syntax at compile time. It provides functions to construct and manipulate located values, parse and check SPARQL query strings using a custom syntax, and generate corresponding OCaml expressions. Concrete use cases include safely embedding SPARQL queries within OCaml programs and ensuring query correctness during compilation.

This module enables embedding SPARQL queries directly in OCaml code, validating their syntax at compile time. It constructs and manipulates located values, parses and checks SPARQL query strings using a custom syntax, and generates corresponding OCaml expressions. Use cases include safely integrating SPARQL queries into OCaml programs and catching query errors during compilation.
